<headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 01 at 5:41PM MDT  by NWS Glasgow</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of east central McCone,
northwestern Dawson and west central Richland Counties through 645 PM
MDT...
At 541 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 14
miles south of Vida, or 15 miles north of Circle, moving east at 20
mph.
HAZARD...Winds in excess of 30 mph and half inch hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.
Locations impacted include...
Richey.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.50 IN
MAX WIND GUST...30 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
